summary: An Ordinance authorizing and directing the City Engineer to incur an indebtedness against the General Fund of the City of Seattle, in the sum of three hundred fifty and no/100 ($350.00) dollars, on account of the cost and expense of the improvement of Dearborn Street, from Twenty-third Avenue South to Twenty-ninth Avenue South, by paving, as authorized by Ordinance No. 23694, creating Local Improvement District No. 2295.
